

=Description=

"The Community Commons working group is intended to provide an access-point for folks interested in commons projects, commons theories, and applied research methods, all designed to engage communities and catalyze social change for the creation and preservation of commons. 

We invite academics, practitioners, enthusiasts, & community members to come together to discuss both implications & applications of the cutting-edge scholarship developed by The Vincent and Elinor Ostrom Workshop in Political Theory and Policy Analysis and by commons experts around the world. 

By inviting a diverse audience to explore a diversity of commons concepts, we seek to cultivate synergies in the interface between commons research and commons practice, 
bringing citizen science to policy science and Workshop wisdom to commons sense."
(http://communitycommonsproject.tumblr.com/colloquia)


